caption: Picked up 2 margherita slices and cracked open a bottle of red wine. DELICIOUS.  I’m writing this as I’m eating my crust with one hand. The dogs are staring - but they won’t win.

Excellent “slice” place (vs. formal restaurant, whole pie type ie. Patsy’s). Is there better? Sure. I could probably make a list. But Homeslice is a throwback to a time when every neighborhood in NYC had more than one decent pizzeria.
Great pizza!

I’m always looking for a great pizzeria. Heard a lot about this place so I decided to visit . I ordered my usual two slices and Diet Coke . I have to say first they were very welcoming and attentive to customers. I noticed that there was a sign that they don’t use sugar and sugar is for cakes. I thought to myself this is even better because I’m always looking to cut on calories when I can. The pizza was classic New York style nice crust had a nice crunch to it yet soft and you can tell they use quality cheese because there’s that bite to it. Believe it or not a lot of places don’t use quality cheese . Sauce has a nice fresh taste to it . I highly recommend this place . Will definitely be coming back.

I must have struck out both times I went here. The first time I tried the Sicilian, BBQ Chicken, and Buffalo (i think). The Sicilian was solid, but both the chickens were frankly not that great, chicken was dry on one of them, cannot remember which.  The second time I went here was right after I went to Joes and Sals (wanted to do a direct slice comparison). I ordered the White Cheese with Spinach and oh my god, it was the worst piece of pizza I have ever had. I'm not even exaggerating, please do not order that slice. The cheese was bad, but the spinach was awful—as if it was straight from a Great Value 99cents can and then spent the entire day  waiting to be served to an unlucky patron like myself.  Will not be returning, too many good options in the area to try for a third time.

Really good pizza! We ordered one of our favorites, Chicken Bacon Ranch and it’s probably in our top 5 of that type of pizza. The crust was especially good. Will definitely order from here again and try other pizzas!

Absolutely, hands down my favorite pizza in New York City. Their regular pizza is amazing but their GRANDMA pizza is the best. My go to spot for sure.

Hands down one of the best pizza spots in all of nyc. I’m a native New Yorker, grew up in Brooklyn from way back in the 90’s, so I know GOOD PIZZA. The pizza is cooked perfectly, and full of flavor.
